    "itinerary": [
      {
        "day": 1,
        "title": "Welcome to New Delhi",
        "description": "Upon arriving at the Delhi International Airport, you will be warmly greeted by a representative holding a personalized placard. From the airport, enjoy a private transfer to your luxury accommodation for the next two nights, the Taj Palace, Delhi. The remainder of your day is entirely at your leisure to relax, overcome jet lag, and enjoy the hotel’s world-class amenities.\n",
        "tags": [
          "Taj palace Delhi"
        ],
        "services": [
          "stay",
          "transfer",
          "sightseeing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "day": 2,
        "title": "The Contrasts of Old and New Delhi",
        "description": "After a delicious breakfast, embark on a full-day guided tour exploring the rich tapestry of India's capital.\nYour morning begins in the winding alleys of Old Delhi. Visit the grand Jama Masjid (India's largest mosque), followed by a thrilling rickshaw ride through the vibrant, aromatic spice markets of Chandni Chowk.\n\nTransitioning into the afternoon, you will explore the historical monuments of New Delhi. Highlights include the imposing Red Fort, Raj Ghat (the peaceful memorial to Mahatma Gandhi), and the stunning Mughal architecture of Humayun's Tomb. Conclude the day with visits to the striking Lotus Temple, the towering 12th-century Qutub Minar, and a drive past the stately Parliament House, President's House, and India Gate.\n\n• Overnight at Taj Palace, Delhi.",
        "tags": [
          "Jama Masjid",
          "Chandni Chowk",
          "Red Fort",
          "Rajghat",
          "Humayun's Tomb",
          "Lotus Temple",
          "Qutub Minar"
        ],
        "services": [
          "breakfast",
          "stay",
          "transfer",
          "sightseeing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "day": 3,
        "title": "Journey to the Mughal Capital, Agra",
        "description": "Following breakfast, you will be chauffeured to the historic city of Agra. Upon arrival, check into the luxurious Taj Hotel & Convention Centre.\nOnce you are refreshed, head out to witness one of the world's most spectacular architectural wonders—the Taj Mahal. Built by Emperor Shah Jahan as a timeless monument of love for his wife, its beauty is truly unmatched \n\nContinue your historical dive with a visit to the massive red sandstone walls of Agra Fort, and finish the day at the delicate Tomb of Itimad-ud-Daulah. Often referred to as the \"Baby Taj,\" this intricately carved tomb is considered the architectural draft for the Taj Mahal itself.\n\n• Overnight at Taj Hotel & Convention Centre, Agra.",
        "tags": [
          "Tajmahal",
          "Tomb of Itimad-ud-Daulah"
        ],
        "services": [
          "stay",
          "transfer",
          "breakfast",
          "sightseeing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "day": 4,
        "title": "Agra to Jaipur via Fatehpur Sikri and Chand Baori",
        "description": "Early risers have the option to return to the Taj Mahal at sunrise, a highly recommended experience to see the marble bathed in golden light. Return to your hotel for breakfast before checking out and beginning your drive to Jaipur, the famed \"Pink City.\"\n\nAlong the way, you will make two fascinating historical stops. First, explore Fatehpur Sikri, the perfectly preserved, deserted red sandstone capital of Emperor Akbar. Next, visit the awe-inspiring Chand Baori in the village of Abhaneri. Plunging 100 feet into the ground with 3,500 narrow, geometric steps, it is one of India's deepest and most visually striking stepwells.\n\nArrive in Jaipur and check into your royal residence, the Taj Jai Mahal Palace. The evening is yours to relax.\n• Overnight at Taj Jai Mahal Palace, Jaipur.",
        "tags": [
          "Fatehpur Sikri",
          "Chand Baori"
        ],
        "services": [
          "breakfast",
          "stay",
          "transfer",
          "sightseeing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "day": 5,
        "title": "Exploring the Pink City",
        "description": "After breakfast, dive into the royal heritage of Rajasthan. Start by ascending the rugged Aravalli Hills to explore the majestic 16th-century Amber Fort (an optional elephant ride to the ramparts is available).\n\nAs you head back into the city, pause for photos at the picturesque Jal Mahal (Water Palace) floating in Man Sagar Lake, and the iconic, multi-windowed Hawa Mahal (Palace of Winds).\n\nIn the afternoon, visit the opulent City Palace and Museum, a magnificent blend of Rajasthani and Mughal architecture designed by Jaipur's founder, Jai Singh. Next door, explore the fascinating Jantar Mantar, a UNESCO-listed open-air astronomical observatory. Spend your late afternoon wandering Jaipur’s bustling local markets, world-renowned for vibrant handicrafts, textiles, and exquisite gold and diamond jewelry.\n\n• Overnight at Taj Jai Mahal Palace, Jaipur.",
        "tags": [
          "Man Sagar Lake",
          "Hawa Mahal"
        ],
        "services": [
          "breakfast",
          "transfer",
          "sightseeing",
          "stay"
        ]
      },
      {
        "day": 6,
        "title": "Jaipur to Delhi & Departure",
        "description": "On your final morning, enjoy a relaxed breakfast before visiting the serene Birla Temple and the fascinating Galta Ji (Monkey Temple), known for its natural springs and resident macaque population.\n\nFollowing your morning exploration, you will be driven back to the Delhi International Airport in your private air-conditioned vehicle, arriving in time for your onward journey with unforgettable memories of India.",
